@startuml 09-private-video-upload

!theme plain
skinparam backgroundColor #FEFEFE
title Flow 9: Private Video Upload (Seal Encryption)

actor "Developer" as Dev
participant "Platform\nBackend" as Backend
participant "Seal\nSDK" as SealSDK
participant "Platform\nSmart Contract" as Contract
database "Sui\nBlockchain" as Sui
database "Walrus\nStorage" as Walrus

== Initiate Private Upload ==

Dev -> Backend: POST /videos/upload\n{title, is_private: true, whitelist: [addr1, addr2]}
Backend -> Backend: Generate random AES key\n(32 bytes)

== Encrypt Video Segments ==

Backend -> Backend: Transcode video to HLS

loop For each HLS segment
    Backend -> Backend: AES.encrypt(segment, aes_key)
end

Backend -> Backend: AES.encrypt(manifest, aes_key)

== Store Encrypted Segments on Walrus ==

loop For each encrypted segment
    Backend -> Walrus: walrus store encrypted_segment
    Walrus --> Backend: blob_id
end

== Encrypt AES Key with Seal ==

Backend -> SealSDK: Seal.encrypt(\n  data: aes_key,\n  packageId: access_policy_pkg,\n  id: video_id,\n  threshold: 2\n)

note right of SealSDK
  Seal encrypts the 32-byte AES key
  using Identity-Based Encryption.

  The "id" ties this key to the
  video's access policy on-chain.
end note

SealSDK --> Backend: encrypted_aes_key

== Register on Sui ==

Backend -> Contract: register_private_video(\n  video_id,\n  blob_ids[],\n  encrypted_aes_key,\n  whitelist[]\n)

Contract -> Sui: Create Video object {\n  is_private: true,\n  encrypted_key: ...,\n  whitelist: [addr1, addr2]\n}

Contract -> Sui: Create Whitelist object {\n  video_id,\n  allowed: [addr1, addr2]\n}

Sui --> Contract: video_id
Contract --> Backend: video_id

Backend --> Dev: Upload complete\n{\n  video_id,\n  playback_url,\n  is_private: true,\n  whitelist: [addr1, addr2]\n}

note right of Backend
  For private videos:
  - All segments are AES encrypted
  - AES key is Seal encrypted
  - Only whitelisted wallets can
    get the decryption key
end note

@enduml
